#95 test: improve code coverage with additional tests
Added tests for previously untested code paths: - perf.rs: tick(), atom(), peak(), total_ticks(), total_atoms(), Default trait - object.rs: error paths in FromStr (invalid format, invalid hex, malformed attributes) - object.rs: xi attribute parsing (with and without xi) - fibonacci.rs: additional Fibonacci calculations - custom_executor.rs: additional emulator execution tests

#95 fix: apply rustfmt formatting to match CI requirements
This commit applies multi-line formatting for: - Struct initializations with multiple fields - Method chains and iterator operations - Macro calls with multiple arguments (assert!, write!, debug!, panic!) - Regex pattern declarations - Result chaining with map_err and ok_or_else
All changes match the exact formatting requirements from the CI rustfmt check.

#95 test: improve test coverage for error paths
Added tests to cover error handling paths in production code: - object.rs: Test for unknown lambda function names - fibonacci.rs: Additional Fibonacci calculation test cases - custom_executor.rs: Tests for emulate() and execute_program() functions
These tests increase code coverage by exercising error handling paths that were previously untested, improving overall test quality without changing production code behavior.
